						               													<description>The players are part of a crew on a spaceship searching for extraterrestial life. Just as they encounter an alien spaceship, several important systems fail, putting the life of the whole crew in danger. Will the aliens help or pose an additional threat?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Escape Adventures is played in two phases: First, the players have to piece together a two-sided, round puzzle. Than they begin to solve puzzles. Some of them require to turn the whole puzzle around, as some important information is only found on one of the sides.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A booklet contains the story of the game that develops as players solve more puzzles. To see if they solved the current puzzle correctly, players use special puzzle tiles to see if their solution forms a continuous line of a specific color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game aims to bring the experience of an Escape Room to the home of the players. It can be played multiple times as no material gets destroyed while playing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
